Solver for all zeros of a complex analytic function that lie within a rectangular region, version 0.0.0.

Copyright (C) 2012 Ivan B. Ivanov. All rights reserved. (navi.adler@gmail.com)

Locating all the zeros of an analytic function in one complex variable that are contained
in a given region of a complex plane is a classical problem of complex analysis.
The standard approach is based on the argument principle and recursive subdivisions of the given region
coupled with the Newton's iterations at the final stage of the search.

The ZerSol library assumes that evaluation of the function is expensive and tries to minimize the number of the function calls
by using of effective algorithms and special data structures.
Although easy to use, the library provides an extensive set of interface functions that allow to customize the search options
for a particular problem. The library is tested on many hard problems and demonstrates a good performance.
